<section id="cold-therapy">
    <h2>Cold Therapy: Instant Vagus Activation</h2>

    <p>Cold is one of the fastest ways to stimulate the vagus nerve. It triggers the "dive reflex" - an ancient survival mechanism.</p>

    <div class="technique-box">
        <h4>Ice Pack Method</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Location:</strong> FRONT of neck (not back)</li>
            <li><strong>Why:</strong> Vagus nerve runs along carotid artery</li>
            <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-3 minutes</li>
            <li><strong>Frequency:</strong> 1-2 times daily</li>
            <li><strong>Effect:</strong> Immediate heart rate drop</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="technique-box">
        <h4>Face Plunge Method</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Fill bowl with cold water + ice</li>
            <li>Take deep breath</li>
            <li>Immerse face for 15-30 seconds</li>
            <li>Feel immediate calm</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="technique-box">
        <h4>Cold Shower Protocol</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Normal warm shower</li>
            <li>Last 30-60 seconds: cold water</li>
            <li>Focus cold on chest/neck</li>
            <li>Breathe slowly and deeply</li>
            <li>Build up duration over time</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>Eye and Face Techniques</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Cold water on eyes:</strong> Splash repeatedly</li>
