            <li>The vibration stimulates vagus nerve</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Bonus:</strong> Singing has same effect - join a choir!</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Gargling: Morning Activation</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Gargle water vigorously for 30 seconds</li>
        <li>Must be intense enough to cause slight discomfort</li>
        <li>Activates muscles innervated by vagus</li>
        <li>Do every morning after brushing teeth</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Laughter Therapy</h3>
    <p>Diaphragmatic movement from real belly laughs massages the vagus nerve. There are actual "laughing clubs" for this reason!</p>

    <h3>Eye Movement Protocol</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Look far right, hold 30 seconds</li>
        <li>Look far left, hold 30 seconds</li>
        <li>Look up, hold 30 seconds</li>
        <li>Look down, hold 30 seconds</li>
        <li>Stimulates vagus through eye muscles</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Valsalva Maneuver</h3>
    <div class="warning-box">
