<section id="hrv">
    <h2>Heart Rate Variability: Measuring Success</h2>

    <p>HRV measures the variation between heartbeats. High HRV = healthy vagus nerve. Low HRV = damaged vagus, high disease risk.</p>

    <h3>Understanding HRV</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Inhale:</strong> Heart rate slightly increases</li>
        <li><strong>Exhale:</strong> Heart rate slightly decreases</li>
        <li><strong>This variation is GOOD</strong></li>
        <li><strong>No variation = vagus damage</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How to Measure</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>HRV apps on phones (using camera)</li>
        <li>Fitness trackers with HRV</li>
        <li>Chest strap monitors</li>
        <li>Measure same time daily (morning best)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Improving Your HRV</h3>
